comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: "381 gross tons. Lbd: 148'6" x 33'2' x 8'7". Wooden twin screw steamship, built 1914 by E. Wright, Cape Hawke, (Tuncurry) New South Wales for Allen Taylor & Co., Sydney. 1919-20 of North Coast S.N. Co., ownership. Sold 1924 to Illawarra & South Coast S N Co., Sydney. 1940-1946 Royal Australian Navy minesweeper, 1951 sold to New Guinea Borneo Mangrove Co., Port Moresby. 1954 broken up Graeme K Andrews" From www.catalogue.lmc.nsw.gov.au/vGallery/VirtualGalleryDetai... Also on the Australian War Memorial website - www.awm.gov.au/collection/301075/

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: Not to be confused (as I did) with another smaller NARANI wrecked at Port Macquarie in 1933 - acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=392701 trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/104477652
